# Day 4 – Windows 11 Domain Join (Active Directory Client Setup)

## Completed:

* Created Windows 11 virtual machine: CLIENT01
* Configured VirtualBox Host-Only networking between DC01 and CLIENT01
* Verified DNS resolution to domain controller (DC01)
* Confirmed connectivity to domain (sandoval.local) via ping and nslookup
* Joined CLIENT01 to Active Directory domain: sandoval.local
* Logged in using domain administrator credentials
* Verified domain authentication works from Windows 11 client

## Domain Join Steps:

* Renamed computer to CLIENT01
* Joined domain: sandoval.local
* Entered domain admin credentials when prompted
* Restarted system to apply domain membership

## Verification:

* Confirmed CLIENT01 is part of sandoval.local domain
* Logged in successfully using:

  * sandoval\Michael
* Tested domain resolution and authentication from client machine

## Break/Fix Issues:

* Fixed VirtualBox Host-Only adapter not binding correctly
* Resolved “network cable unplugged” issue on CLIENT01
* Corrected DNS configuration pointing CLIENT01 to DC01
* Fixed domain join issues caused by incorrect network attachment
* Resolved login issues caused by incorrect username formatting

